<h2 style="text-align: center;">Military Caregiver Leave</h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Military caregiver leave is taken by a spouse, parent, child, or&nbsp;</span><a href="/resources-and-guides/frequently-asked-questions/glossary-of-terms">next of kin</a><span style="background-color: #ffffff; letter-spacing: 0.0204px; color: #5f5f5f;">&nbsp;to care for a&nbsp;</span><a href="/resources-and-guides/frequently-asked-questions/glossary-of-terms">covered service member</a><span style="background-color: #ffffff; letter-spacing: 0.0204px; color: #5f5f5f;">&nbsp;who incurred a serious injury or illness in the line of duty on active duty in the Armed Forces.</span></p>
